episodes.title: An Alien on the Planet
episodes.plot: An alien invites himself into Tsutsui's apartment, and hilarity ensues.

episodes.title: Run After the Man
episodes.plot: Captain Craft and two officers come to Earth to retrieve Yukitaka's resident alien. The leader of the Diskunians warns them that they will kill anyone who crosses their paths. Unfortunately, Yukitaka's houseguest manages to do just that.

episodes.title: Risky Game!
episodes.plot: The prince of Dogra has insulted the Diskunians and now they want his head. Yukitaka and Miho find themselves in the middle of what could result in an intergalactic war. The only way out of this mess is lost together with the prince's memories!

episodes.title: From the Darkness
episodes.plot: Four high school boys see one someone from their school devour a girl. They want to know who it is, so they can steer clear of the monster. When the boys begin disappearing one by one, the remaining boys decide it's time to get professional help.

episodes.title: Here Come Color Tanger!!
episodes.plot: Prince Baka kidnaps an innocent group of young boys, turns them into his own private fighting force, and orders them to attack their teacher!

episodes.title: Dancing in the Trap!!
episodes.plot: The Color Rangers rush to obtain the key needed to remove their transformation bracelets. When they go to school the next day, they get transported to an RPG world. Now they must level up if they hope to beat the game and go home.

episodes.title: Game Over...!?
episodes.plot: The Demon King has reprogrammed the monsters, making it too dangerous for the Color Rangers and Baka to stay. Unfortunately, the game console and the only spaceship on the planet are in the Demon King's castle, which is guarded by a horde of monsters.

episodes.title: You're my Darling!
episodes.plot: Princess Saki has come to Earth to find a mate. If she finds one and has intercourse with him, the human race will be extinct within just a few generations. Craft, Sade and Colin must do anything they can to prevent Saki from finding her Mr. Perfect.

episodes.title: Love Me Tender
episodes.plot: In a desperate attempt to tear Saki from Mikihisa, Craft tells the alien princess that Mikihisa is a girl. Saki acts so heartbroken that she leaves Earth early. Craft believes he has rescued Earth, but things aren't always as they seem...

episodes.title: Boy Meets Girl
episodes.plot: A group of poachers have brought one of the last Twin-tail Mermaids in the universe to Earth. When Shimizu finds her injured, he decides it is up to the Color Rangers to save her. This will be the Color Rangers' last fight together...

episodes.title: Field of Dreams!
episodes.plot: Yukitaka and his school baseball team are on the bus headed for regionals. On the way there, everyone suddenly gets transported to an alternate Koushien in someone's mind. They must figure out how to return to the real world before it's game time.

episodes.title: Half Moon...!
episodes.plot: Princess Luna has come to Earth to marry Prince Baka. If he doesn't marry her within a month, he will lose his claim to the throne. Baka must avoid both his fiancÃ©e and his younger brother for one month or else his days of fun will come to an end.

episodes.title: Full Moon...!
episodes.plot: Princess Luna and Prince Mohan aren't who they claim to be! Prince Baka sees through their disguises only to learn that the planet Earth is in danger once more. This time the fate of both Dogra and Earth rest in his hands.
